{"id":"2109.12825","submitter":"Yuta Nakahara","authors":"Yuta Nakahara, Shota Saito, Akira Kamatsuka, Toshiyasu Matsushima","title":"Probability Distribution on Full Rooted Trees","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Entropy 2022, 24(3), 328","doi":"10.3390/e24030328","report-no":null,"categories":"stat.ML cs.DM cs.LG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The recursive and hierarchical structure of full rooted trees is applicable\nto represent statistical models in various areas, such as data compression,\nimage processing, and machine learning. In most of these cases, the full rooted\ntree is not a random variable; as such, model selection to avoid overfitting\nbecomes problematic. A method to solve this problem is to assume a prior\ndistribution on the full rooted trees. This enables the optimal model selection\nbased on the Bayes decision theory. For example, by assigning a low prior\nprobability to a complex model, the maximum a posteriori estimator prevents the\nselection of the complex one. Furthermore, we can average all the models\nweighted by their posteriors. In this paper, we propose a probability\ndistribution on a set of full rooted trees. Its parametric representation is\nsuitable for calculating the properties of our distribution using recursive\nfunctions, such as the mode, expectation, and posterior distribution. Although\nsuch distributions have been proposed in previous studies, they are only\napplicable to specific applications. Therefore, we extract their mathematically\nessential components and derive new generalized methods to calculate the\nexpectation, posterior distribution, etc.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Sep 2021 06:51:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Oct 2021 17:24:44 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 6 Nov 2021 13:29:40 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 23 Jan 2022 16:50:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-24"}
